{"id": 231964750, "title": "Man, 20, rushed to hospital after serious assault as police launch probe", "text": "Detectives are appealing for information after a man was seriously assaulted in Blantyre. A 20-year-old man was rushed to hospital for treatment following the incident around 3am on Saturday, 8 June, 2024 on Logan Street. Detective Constable Sharon McBride is appealing for anyone with dashcam footage to come forward. She said: \u201cOur enquiries are ongoing and we are appealing to anyone who may have information to contact us. \u201cWe are also asking people to check private CCTV and dash-cams for footage that could assist with our investigation.\u201d Anyone who can help is asked to contact police on 101, quoting incident 0868 of 8 June, 2024. Alternatively, Crimestoppers can be contacted on 0800 555 111, where anonymity can be maintained. Don't miss the latest news from around Scotland and beyond - Sign up to our daily newsletter here.", "summary": "A 20-year-old man was rushed to hospital following a serious assault.", "url": "https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/man-20-rushed-hospital-after-32992374", "image": "https://i2-prod.dailyrecord.co.uk/incoming/article32992386.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_police-car.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 13:04:20", "author": "Jolene Campbell", "authors": ["Jolene Campbell"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.368}